column5: I left my packing until after dark, the day before we left, not a good idea, panic power packing!    Blueberry Road at 6am    "Audio, audio, check, 1,2, do you copy?"    I can't complain about the weather, no rain during daylight hours, it did go from warm    then cool, fall like weather mid week    then it got hot at the end of the week  cannibalistic pike      the black flies, skeeters and horse flies were bad, the screened in porch at camp was awesome    if it was pickerel dinner, the first guys awake in the morning would go out and grab the fish, get them cleaned and in the fridge, then just beer drink and enjoy fishing the rest of the day with the dirty work already done    it's a rocky lake, these prop guards are necessary    Teagan, the newest member demonstrates the Leuenberger pickerel hold    my contribution to Eddie's camp, well, Eddie's outhouse actually    huuuge water to explore      a long battle with a pike on a walleye rig    shore lunch    my Dad got the big pike of the trip, 18 lbs, here's the release    it's an awesome lake, we all said we would like to do it again, with Beteau, Windsor, and now Blackbirch, Eddie's options are hard to beat
Nice report Good to see you introducing the young lad to the Canadian Wilderness.
Glad it went well Chris! Was expecting a call from you to go over the map before you left. Based on the last pic can I assume they still weren't able to dock the plane at the camp?

Glad it went well Chris! Was expecting a call from you to go over the map before you left. Based on the last pic can I assume they still weren't able to dock the plane at the camp?  a few times during the week, I said to whoever I was in the boat with "damn!, I should have called Solo (that's what they know you as) to go over the map!"  good eye, beach drop off and pick up, but it's not a big deal when there's already boats there, unlike your trip
Good job, mr. Solid.  Looks like a great time, and looks like they even have you guys set up with four strokes?
Nice report Chris thanks for sharing.
Sounds like you had a great trip up there Chris, beautiful spot too from the looks of it.
Great report and nice golden walleye. I like the idea of that prop/skeg guard. I could have used one a time or two in the past. Was this store bought, or manufactured in your garage?
Good times Chris! Thanks for sharing!  S.
Betcha caught a pile of walleye didn't ya?  Nice report!
nothing like limiting out and spending the rest of the day drinking beers laid back...  great report.
I don't think you can go wrong with any of Eddie's camps.  Nice report!
Nice report Chris, wish I was back there again .
Nice report Chris, i noticed the old green Bantam Curado in the forth slide, one of the most dependable low profiles ever made, definately a reel you can take away on a fly in with confidence
Great report Chris  Thanks for taking the time!!  Lots of water to explore!!  For Sure!!  Rick
great trip chris look's like you guy's had a good time
